 security\" and that it had refused to co-operate with the Turkish authorities.</p><p>Erdoğan claimed audio postings were part of a plot contrived by his political enemies to unseat him ahead of the nationwide local elections on Sunday, which are widely being seen as a referendum on his 11-year rule.</p><p>Reuters has not been able to verify the authenticity of the recordings.</p><p>Telecoms regulators have said their blockage was based on four court orders and was imposed after complaints from citizens that Twitter was violating privacy.</p>","headline":"Turkish court upholds appeal against ban on Twitter","trailText":"Block imposed by Turkey's telecoms authority ahead of elections has not yet been removed <br />","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/3/26/1395835700771/Turkish-Prime-Minister-Re-006.jpg","wordcount":"240","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-03-29T12:17:36Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2014/mar/26/turkish-court-upholds-appeal-end-block-twitter-recep-tayyip-erdogan","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/technology/2014/mar/26/turkish-court-upholds-appeal-end-block-twitter-recep-tayyip-erdogan","tags":[{"id":"technology/twitter","webTitle":"Twitter","type":"keyword","sectionId":"technology","sectionName":"Technology","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/technology/twitter","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/technology/twitter","references":[]},{"id":"world/turkey","webTitle":"Turkey","type":"keyword","sectionId":"world","sectionName":"World news","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/world/turkey","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/world/turkey","references":[]},{"id":"tone/news","webTitle":"News","type":"tone","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/tone/news","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/tone/news","references":[]},{"id":"type/article","webTitle":"Article","type":"type","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/articles","apiUrl":"http